<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="494" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1811,2018]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,150,285]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="494" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1847,1873]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jewett, S. G." box="[665,834,1847,1874]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref9121" refString="Jewett, S. G. (1960 b) Two new species of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera) from Goias, Brazil. Contributions in Science, 36, 1 - 4. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / p. 241035" type="journal article" year="1960">Jewett (1960b)</bibRefCitation>
based on specimens from the region of Formoso and São João da Aliança, in the north of Goiás state. According to the author, the type series would be deposited in the National Museum of Rio de Janeiro, RJ, BR (
<typeStatus box="[657,758,1919,1945]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">holotype</typeStatus>
) and NHM (Natural History Museum, Los Angeles County), CA, 
<collectingCountry box="[205,259,1955,1981]" name="United States of America" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<typeStatus box="[276,390,1955,1981]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">paratypes</typeStatus>
). However, the 
<typeStatus box="[569,667,1955,1981]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">holotype</typeStatus>
is misplaced. Fortunately, a 
<typeStatus box="[994,1090,1956,1982]" pageId="6" pageNumber="493">paratype</typeStatus>
was located in the NHM. The specimen is pinned female. Despite being well preserved and having a color pattern corresponding to the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Jewett, S. G." box="[292,449,151,177]" pageId="7" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref9121" refString="Jewett, S. G. (1960 b) Two new species of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera) from Goias, Brazil. Contributions in Science, 36, 1 - 4. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / p. 241035" type="journal article" year="1960">Jewett 1960b</bibRefCitation>
), in the picture (
<figureCitation box="[639,708,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1361,1385]" captionTargetBox="[173,1406,309,1335]" captionTargetId="figure-82@7.[151,1435,309,1337]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Female paratype adult of Anacroneuria dourada. A: head and pronotum; B: subgenital plate; C: collection event and museum labels; D: determination label." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816769" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816769/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="494">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) the subgenital plate is a little collapsed, not allowing a deeper analysis. The morphology of this 
<typeStatus box="[527,623,187,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="494">paratype</typeStatus>
needs to be carefully studied before checking the possibility of associating it with the specimens collected in the type locality in north Goiás state. Additionally, the fact that the 
<typeStatus box="[1340,1436,223,249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="494">paratype</typeStatus>
is female can hinder this process.
</paragraph>
